      "picks_file": "picks/picks-2026-06-06-1722.md",
      "why_text": "For the first time, Texas has surpassed California in the number of Fortune 500 headquarters \u2014 a symbolic gut-punch to a state that once defined American corporate ambition. The shift reflects years of high taxes, regulatory burden, and cost-of-living pressure driving companies like Tesla, Oracle, and Hewlett Packard Enterprise to relocate to friendlier business climates in the Lone Star State. This isn't just an economic footnote; it's a reordering of which state gets to claim the identity of American capitalism.",
      "last_escalated_item_ids": [
        "5e2abe150c7e",
        "ee86309679dc",
        "7cb0cb419756"
      ]
    },
