      "why_text": "Victor Wembanyama's late-game turnover \u2014 with Karl-Anthony Towns reportedly central to the play \u2014 cost San Antonio a win they had in hand, and Wemby's own postgame admission that 'this game was ours' makes it sting harder. It's a brutal lesson for the 20-year-old phenom: individual brilliance means nothing when the moment slips through your hands. The Spurs are still rebuilding, but losses like this one \u2014 winnable, self-inflicted \u2014 are the exact growing pains that define whether a generational talent becomes a generational winner.",
